            <div class="read-more-content">
                 MASTRANTONI, Romeo<br />
<br />
It is with great sadness that we announce the sudden passing of Romeo. He passed away at home surrounded by his family, at the age of 66. Beloved son of Francesca and the late Giacomo (1973). Romeo is survived by his loving wife of 40 years, Maria and sons Giacomo (Sonia) and Andrea. Adoring Nonno to Aria. Loving son in-law of Anita Di Bartolomeo, and the late Roberto Di Bartolomeo. Cherished brother to Santa (Gino Mauti) and Concetta (Domenic Di Prospero), brother-in-law to Lidia (Giovanni Piedimonte). He will always be remembered by his nieces, nephews, family and numerous friends. <br />
<br />
Romeo was the happiest when he was surrounded by his family. He valued being together and was the pillar of his familys closeness.<br />
<br />
A highly respected, hardworking and skilled carpenter, framer and builder, Romeo was truly a jack of all trades. There is nothing he couldnt do or wouldnt do for his family. He began working at the age of fourteen in Italy, to help support his family.<br />
<br />
Romeo had a passion for life. He was kind, generous and loving. Even in his final moments, he always greeted his loved ones with a smile and a warm embrace. He will be forever cherished and loved.<br />
<br />
Visitation will be held at Bernardo Funeral Homes (2960 Dufferin St., Toronto, south of Lawrence Ave. W.) on Sunday, March 21, 2021 from 2-8 p.m. Due to the COVID-19 restrictions, attendees will need to reserve a time slot for visitation. Below, please click the blue RSVP button to make your reservation.<br />
<br />
A private funeral Mass will be held on Monday, March 22, 2021 at 10:00 a.m. Relatives and friends are welcomed to participate online virtually on St. Fidelis website:<br />
<br />
<a href="https://stfidelis.ca">https://stfidelis.ca</a><br />
<br />
A private entombment will follow at Westminster Cemetery.<br />
<br />
If desired, donations may be made to the Heart and Stroke Foundation of Canada.
